Sentencas: The key issue that limits the electrochemical performance of proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H+-SOFCs) is the sluggish kinetics of the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) of cathode at intermediate and low temperatures.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, oxygen vacancy engineering is conducted on cobalt-free Ba0.95La0.05FeO3-delta (BLF) by nickel substitution, which is confirmed by density functional theory computations.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nickel-substituted BLF material (Ba0.95La0.05Fe1-xNixO3-delta (x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3)) can promote the generation of oxygen vacancies and improve catalytic activity, which is found to be in line with the experimental results of XPS.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase structure, microstructure, and electrochemical performance of Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-delta (BLFNi0.2) are well-investigated.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cells with the BLFNi0.2-BaCe0.7Zr0.1Y0.1Yb0.1O3-delta (BCZYYb) composite cathode achieve low polari-zation resistance (Rp) of 0.099 omega cm(2) and a peak power density of 631 mW cm-2 at 700 C while maintaining good durability for 120 h with no observable degradation.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that Ni-doped BLF is a promising cobalt-free cathode material for H+-SOFCs.
Titulo: Ba0.95La0.05Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-? perovskite as efficient cathode electrocatalysts for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
